    "When misclassification costs are inadequately defined and heavily weighted towards the minority classes, CSL methods can exhibit excessive adaptation to these classes (Sun et al. 2011), which may lead to overfitting (Elrahman and Abraham 2013) and reduced generalization performance.",
    "Therefore, thoughtful attention should be paid to defining the costs, ensuring their appropriateness, and mitigating the risks associated with excessive adaptation.",
    "Transitioning to the analysis of CSL approaches, it is essential to acknowledge their inheritance of the broader advantages and disadvantages of CSL.",
